instruction: Analyze the chart data provided and explain the differences in positioning between sell-side market participants and asset managers/institutional investors.
output: Based on the chart data provided, it is clear that sell-side market participants have consistently held net-short positions on futures linked to MSCI indexes over the years. This suggests that these participants are primarily interested in hedging their risk across markets and clients, rather than speculating on the direction of the underlying assets. On the other hand, asset managers and institutional investors have held net-long positions over these years, indicating a more bullish outlook on the MSCI indexes. This difference in positioning is likely due to the differing investment strategies and goals of these types of market participants.
